%N A395397 Decimal expansion of the volume of the solid of revolution formed by rotating the loop part of a Folium of Descartes about its axis of symmetry.
%C A395397 The Folium of Descartes is a plane curve that can be described by x^3 + y^3 = 3*a*x*y. Here we take a = 1.
%C A395397 Its axis of symmetry is the line y = x.
%D A395397 N. P. Bali and Usha Paul, A Textbook of Engineering Mathematics: for B.E., B.Tech. Semester I, Laxmi Publications (P) Ltd, 8th ed., 2014, pp. 139-140.
%H A395397 Doand A. Cole, <a href="https://www.mathematicsasart.com/mystery-of-the-sor">The Mystery of the SOR</a>.
%H A395397 Amiram Eldar, <a href="/A395397/a395397.png">Illustration of the solid of revolution</a>.
%H A395397 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/FoliumofDescartes.html">Folium of Descartes</a>.
%H A395397 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Folium_of_Descartes">Folium of Descartes</a>.
%F A395397 Equals (Pi/(6*sqrt(2))) * (8*log(2)-3).
